<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-08T12:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-08T12:40:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1060: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-08T13:00:00-04:40">February 8, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5. My telegram 4, February 7, 8 p.m. Minister of Foreign Affairs is
                            sending telegraphic representation to Peru today specifically based on
                            Kellogg Pact. Am sending copy to Department by the next pouch.<note n="13" xml:id="d480fn13">Transmitted in despatch No. 797, February
                                8, not printed.</note> He confirms that Dominican Government has not
                            received from Colombia, as other signatory Governments apparently
                            received, request to make representations based on Pact for Renunciation
                            of War.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>